µC1Ghandy: How do you see the future of the demoscene in the ideal case? Will in five years oscar nominations or the award of a golden globe happen for a demo?

µC8Poti: The Demoscene is mostly less glamurous and more native. I see less connections to an Oscar or a Golden Globe. Anyway, I prefer if others speak the oracles. Many people also speak since fifteen years of the death of the Scene. A bit problematic is in fact the question of new junior employees.

µC8But more interesting for me would be how the asthetic of the scene envolves, and how it will handle narrative elements.



µC1Ghandy: At the beginning the computer scene was something secret, something dubious. Does it make sense to show a wide audience such an underground movement, which was only known by real insiders?

µC8Poti: What we mostly present ar the productions of the demoscene. And those demos and intros have been done in order to be seen from as many people as possible.

µC8When it comes to demoparties, we try to hide them a bit from the public. We don't have anything about articles after the party is over, surely also when it comes to our sponsors. But we don't spread informations before the party takes place. Excursions of daddies with their boys or with the complete family are not what we want.

µC1(Note from Ghandy: Then they would visit a demoparty and watch us demosceners instead of going to a zoo ;-) µC8  But otherwise we naturally don't have anything against interested visitors.



